line_1: And there, scarce less illustrious, goes the clerk.
line_2: There goes the parson, oh! illustrious spark,

line_1: For many a grave and learned clerk,
line_2: And many a gay unletter'd spark,
Yet fears to travel in the dark,

line_1: Who takes no bribe, and keeps no Clerk)
line_2: Before whom nothing's in the dark,

line_1: ' Howl thro' the dwelling o' the CLERK!
